        <T> void putCommandModifier(java.lang.Class<T> propertyType,
                            java.util.function.BiConsumer<T,CommandHandleBuilder> configurator)
        The provided configurator is used to modify commands that possess the specified property. If there is an existing modifier it is overridden.
        Type Parameters:
        T - the propertyType
        Parameters:
        propertyType - the class of the property
        configurator - a BiConsumer. The first argument is the property. The second argument is the CommandHandleBuilder the property is attached to.

      • appendCommandModifier

        <T> void appendCommandModifier(java.lang.Class<T> propertyType,
                               java.util.function.BiConsumer<T,CommandHandleBuilder> configurator)
        The provided configurator is used to modify commands that possess the specified property. If there is an existing modifier, the passed BiConsumer is appended to the end of it so that it is applied to the builder after the existing one has been applied.
        Type Parameters:
        T - the propertyType
        Parameters:
        propertyType - the class of the property
        configurator - a BiConsumer. The first argument is the property. The second argument is the CommandHandleBuilder the property is attached to.
